THIRD-PARTY ATTRIBUTION

This project ports and adapts algorithms from the Vortex Tracker II (VTII)
project family, originally written for ZX Spectrum. The MIT license above
covers the original code in this repository (the CA65 6502 implementation,
the Python reference simulator wrapper code, the test harness, build tools,
and documentation). Portions derived from VTII source code remain governed
by their original authors' release terms — see THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md for
the complete inventory and attribution.

In short, the third-party material is:

  - Pattern decode and playback logic (trfuncs.pas)
      © 2000–2009 Sergey Bulba
      © 2017–2019 Ivan Pirog
      Released as part of Vortex Tracker II source distribution at
      bulba.untergrund.net and on GitHub (z00m128/vortextracker25).

  - Note frequency table generator (NoteTableCreator)
  - Volume table generator (VolTableCreator)
      Originally written by Ivan Roshin for the Z80 player VTII10 r7,
      © 2004–2007 Sergey Bulba.
      Released as part of the VTII Z80 player source.

We are deeply grateful to these authors. Their decades of work on the
PT3 format — and their decision to release the source publicly — are
what made this project possible.
